President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring April 19th to April 27th, 2014 as National Park Week. During this week, the National Park Service will offer free admission to national parks in order to encourage Americans to explore and appreciate the natural beauty and cultural heritage of their country. The proclamation also highlights the 30th anniversary of the first National Heritage Area, a program that preserves historic sites and helps future generations understand American history. President Obama mentions his efforts to establish new National Monuments, which honor American heroes and conserve wildlife and landscapes. He emphasizes the economic value of national parks, as they attract tourists and support local businesses. The proclamation concludes by encouraging all Americans to visit their National Parks and celebrate the blessings they offer.